      "extra": {
        "message": "Weak PRNG for File Naming\n\nrandom.randint(1, 100) is used to generate a prefix for uploaded filenames. The range is extremely small (1-100), making collisions very likely and filenames predictable.\n\nImpact: Uploaded files can be overwritten due to predictable naming. An attacker could predict filenames to access or overwrite other users' uploads.\n\nFix: Use uuid.uuid4() or os.urandom() for generating unique, unpredictable filenames.",
        "severity": "LOW",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-338"
